  "bib_entries": {
    "8950935": {
      "title": "Acute and chronic toxicity of an aqueous fraction of the stem bark of Stryphnodendron adstringens (Barbatimão) in rodents",
      "abstract": "Stryphnodendron adstringens has a high tannin content and is used as an antiseptic and antimicrobial and in the treatment of leucorrhea, gonorrhea, wound healing, and gastritis. The present study evaluated the toxic effects of the heptamer prodelphinidin (F2) from the stem bark of S. adstringens in rodents. In the acute toxicity test, the mice that received oral doses exhibited reversible effects, with an LD50 of 3.015 . In the chronic toxicity test at 90 days, Wistar rats were treated with different doses of F2 (10, 100, and 200 ). In the biochemical, hematological, and histopathological examinations and open-field test, the different dose groups did not exhibit significant differences compared with controls. The present results indicate that F2 from the stem bark of S. adstringens caused no toxicity with acute and chronic oral treatment in rodents at the doses administered."
    }
